<subSubSection id="C365CEF6772EFF8A4EA958D1FE47A91E" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BC09D7D772EFF8A4EA958D1FE47A91E" blockId="77.[151,1437,1380,2042]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis id="B90B416F772EFF8A4EA958D1FE89A971" bold="true" box="[199,294,1768,1794]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Ecology</emphasis>
. Intertidal and shallow subtidal, presently known depth range 
<quantity id="4C873098772EFF8A4DB958D1FB82A970" box="[983,1069,1768,1795]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" unit="m" value="18.0" valueMax="36.0" valueMin="0.0">0–36 m</quantity>
, usually in waters shallower than 
<quantity id="4C873098772EFF8A4EF95932FF6BA955" box="[151,196,1803,1830]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" unit="m" value="6.0">6 m</quantity>
; on rocky shores and mixed rock-rubble-sand bottoms, typically under large rocks and boulders, often encrusted by coralline algae and sponges, or in rock crevices (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEEE08C772EFF8A4CBC5916FCE4A93A" author="Haig, J." box="[722,843,1839,1865]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="57 - 74" refId="ref72890" refString="Haig, J. (1968) Eastern Pacific expeditions of the New York Zoological Society. Porcellanid crabs (Crustacea: Anomura) from the west coast of tropical America. Zoologica, New York, 53 (2), 57 - 74." type="journal article" year="1968">Haig 1968</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEEE08C772EFF8A4D385916FBF6A93A" author="Hiller, A. &amp; Werding, B." box="[854,1113,1839,1865]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="181 - 194" refId="ref73657" refString="Hiller, A. &amp; Werding, B. (2007) Redescription of Petrolisthes edwardsii (de Saussure) and description of a new, sibling species from the eastern Pacific based on different colour, morphology and genetic identity (Crustacea: Anomura: Porcellanidae). Organisms Diversity and Evolution, 7 (3), 181 - 194. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ode. 2006.06.002" type="journal article" year="2007">Hiller &amp; Werding 2007</bibRefCitation>
; García-Madrigal &amp; Andréu- Sánchez 2009; present study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C365CEF6772EFF884EA9594CFE48AC6A" lastPageId="79" lastPageNumber="80" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC09D7D772EFF8A4EA9594CFDA7A989" blockId="77.[151,1437,1380,2042]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis id="B90B416F772EFF8A4EA9594CFE9BA9FC" bold="true" box="[199,308,1909,1935]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Remarks</emphasis>
. All records of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7FE6FE772EFF8A4F9E594FFDD4A9FC" baseAuthorityName="de Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[496,635,1909,1935]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edwardsii">
<emphasis id="B90B416F772EFF8A4F9E594FFDD4A9FC" box="[496,635,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. edwardsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
prior to the study of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEEE08C772EFF8A4D15594CFB34A9FC" author="Hiller, A. &amp; Werding, B." box="[891,1179,1909,1935]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="181 - 194" refId="ref73657" refString="Hiller, A. &amp; Werding, B. (2007) Redescription of Petrolisthes edwardsii (de Saussure) and description of a new, sibling species from the eastern Pacific based on different colour, morphology and genetic identity (Crustacea: Anomura: Porcellanidae). Organisms Diversity and Evolution, 7 (3), 181 - 194. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ode. 2006.06.002" type="journal article" year="2007">Hiller &amp; Werding (2007)</bibRefCitation>
are uncertain because of its sympatric co-occurrence with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7FE6FE772EFF8A4C5A59A0FD02A9C1" authorityName="Hiller &amp; Werding" authorityYear="2007" box="[564,685,1944,1970]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="donadio">
<emphasis id="B90B416F772EFF8A4C5A59A0FD02A9C1" box="[564,685,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. donadio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except for the original description and material verified by these authors. As mentioned above, the two species can be most easily distinguished when alive, by their diagnostic colour patterns (cf. 
<figureCitation id="134481F8772EFF8A4F1C59E6FE53A989" box="[370,508,2015,2042]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 42" captionStart-1="FIGURE 43" captionStart-2="FIGURE 44" captionStart-3="FIGURE 45" captionStartId-0="76.[151,250,1920,1944]" captionStartId-1="78.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionStartId-2="79.[151,250,1914,1938]" captionStartId-3="80.[151,250,1332,1356]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1435,181,1896]" captionTargetBox-1="[189,1398,181,1889]" captionTargetBox-2="[164,1423,561,1891]" captionTargetBox-3="[177,1411,181,1308]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@76.[151,1435,181,1896]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@78.[189,1398,181,1889]" captionTargetId-2="figure-205@79.[164,1423,561,1891]" captionTargetId-3="figure-19@80.[177,1411,181,1308]" captionTargetPageId-0="76" captionTargetPageId-1="78" captionTargetPageId-2="79" captionTargetPageId-3="80" captionText-0="FIGURE 42. Petrolisthes donadio Hiller &amp; Werding, 2007: A–C, ovigerous female (cl 10.7 mm, cw 10.1 mm) from Coiba Island, Panama (FLMNH UF 57711), dorsal (A), ventral (B) and frontal (C) views [photographs by AA]." captionText-1="FIGURE 43. Petrolisthes edwardsii (Saussure, 1853): A–C, male (cl 15.1 mm, cw 15.7 mm) from Coiba Island, Panama (FLMNH UF 57143), dorsal (A), ventral (B) and frontodorsal (C) views [photographs by AA]." captionText-2="FIGURE 44. Petrolisthes edwardsii (Saussure, 1853): A, B, ovigerous female (cl cw indet.) from Taboga Island, Panama (not deposited), dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views [photographs by AA]." captionText-3="FIGURE 45. Comparison of anterior regions of Petrolisthes donadio Hiller &amp; Werding, 2007 [A–C] and Petrolisthes edwardsii (Saussure, 1853) [D –F]: A–C ovigerous female (cl 10.7 mm, cw 10.1 mm) from Coiba Island, Panama (FLMNH UF 57711); D–F, male (cl 15.1 mm, cw 15.7 mm) from Coiba Island, Panama (FLMNH UF 57143); A, D, frontal region of carapace, antennules and Mxp3, dorsal view; B, E, Mxp3 and antennules, ventral view; C, F, frontal region with Mxp3 and other mouthparts, frontal view [photographs by AA]." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532303" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532309" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532311" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532315" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5532303/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5532309/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5532311/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/5532315/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Figs. 42–45</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF00CDF5772DFF894EF95941FBF7A9C6" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532309" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5532309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532309/files/figure.png" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" startId="78.[151,250,1912,1936]" targetBox="[189,1398,181,1889]" targetPageId="78">
<paragraph id="8BC09D7D772DFF894EF95941FBF7A9C6" blockId="78.[151,1436,1912,1973]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis id="B90B416F772DFF894EF95941FEB3A9E3" bold="true" box="[151,284,1912,1936]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">FIGURE 43</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7FE6FE772DFF894F435941FD62A9E3" authority="(Saussure, 1853)" baseAuthorityName="de Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[301,717,1912,1937]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edwardsii">
<emphasis id="B90B416F772DFF894F435941FDBDA9E3" box="[301,530,1912,1936]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Petrolisthes edwardsii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEEE08C772DFF894C4D5940FD6AA9E3" author="Saussure, H. de" box="[547,709,1912,1937]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" pagination="354 - 368" refId="ref76288" refString="Saussure, H. de (1853) Description de quelques crustaces nouveaux de la cote occidentale du Mexique. Revue et Magasin de Zoologie Pure et Apliquee, 2 (5), 354 - 368." type="journal article" year="1853">Saussure, 1853</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
: A–C, male (cl 15.1 mm, cw 15.7 mm) from Coiba Island, Panama (FLMNH UF 57143), dorsal (A), ventral (B) and frontodorsal (C) views [photographs by AA].
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BC09D7D772CFF884EA95EAEFE48AC6A" blockId="79.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
The Mexican specimens reported as 
<taxonomicName id="4C7FE6FE772CFF884C025EAEFCB3AEC2" baseAuthorityName="de Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[620,796,151,177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edwardsii">
<emphasis id="B90B416F772CFF884C025EAEFD2EAEC3" box="[620,641,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">P.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B90B416F772CFF884CC15EAEFCB3AEC2" box="[687,796,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">edwardsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEEE08C772CFF884D255EAEFA94AEC2" author="Garcia-Madrigal, M. S. &amp; Andreu-Sanchez, L. I." box="[843,1339,151,177]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" pagination="23 - 54" refId="ref71705" refString="Garcia-Madrigal, M. S. &amp; Andreu-Sanchez, L. I. (2009) Los cangrejos porcelanidos (Decapoda: Anomura) del Pacifico sur de Mexico, incluyendo una lista y clave de identificacion para todas las especies del Pacifico oriental tropical. Ciencia y Mar, 13 (39), 23 - 54." type="journal article" year="2009">García-Madrigal &amp; Andréu-Sánchez (2009)</bibRefCitation>
seem to present a slightly different colour pattern, although the specimen in their colour photograph is clearly discoloured (perhaps from a recent preservation or 
<emphasis id="B90B416F772CFF884C2B5EE6FD7CAE8B" box="[581,723,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">post-mortem</emphasis>
condition) and appears more orange, with less red on the bumps and tubercles (
<emphasis id="B90B416F772CFF884F505F3AFEDBAF6E" box="[318,372,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">idem</emphasis>
: fig. 3D). An 
<emphasis id="B90B416F772CFF884C785F3AFDF3AF6F" box="[534,604,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">in situ</emphasis>
photograph of a living crab from Los Cabos, Gulf of California (see 
<figureCitation id="134481F8772CFF884B1E5F3AFF68AF32" captionStart="FIGURE 89" captionStartId="139.[151,250,1809,1833]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,181,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-19@139.[189,1398,181,1785]" captionTargetPageId="139" captionText="FIGURE 89. Some eastern Pacific Porcellanidae (all species reported from Panama) photographed in situ: A, Pachycheles vicarius Nobili, 1901, Bahía Málaga, Colombia; B, C, Petrolisthes edwardsii (de Saussure, 1853), Los Cabos, Baja California, Mexico (B), and Malpelo Island, Colombia (C); D, Petrolisthes donadio Hiller &amp; Werding, 2007, Malpelo Island, Colombia, near sea urchin, Diadema mexicanum Agassiz; E, Petrolisthes glasselli Haig, 1957, Malpelo Island, Colombia; F, Petrolisthes haigae Chace, 1962, Malpelo Island, Colombia [photographs courtesy of Juan-Felipe Lazarus-Agudelo (A, C–F) and Jeff Goddard (B)]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532432/files/figure.png" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Fig. 89B</figureCitation>
) shows that the colour pattern of the Mexican specimens is generally very similar to that of the Panamanian specimens, including the characteristic bright-blue and black Mxp3. This observation is important, since Mazatlán, 
<collectingCountry id="F368DDED772CFF884EF95F56FF40AFFA" box="[151,239,367,393]" name="Mexico" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, is the 
<typeStatus id="54C423DF772CFF884F545F56FEC5AFFA" box="[314,362,367,393]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7FE6FE772CFF884F895F56FDC0AFFA" baseAuthorityName="de Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[487,623,367,393]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edwardsii">
<emphasis id="B90B416F772CFF884F895F56FDC0AFFA" box="[487,623,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">P. edwardsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, supporting the view of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7FE6FE772CFF884D155F56FBADAFFA" baseAuthorityName="de Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[891,1026,367,393]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edwardsii">
<emphasis id="B90B416F772CFF884D155F56FBADAFFA" box="[891,1026,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">P. edwardsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a species widely distributed in the tropical eastern Pacific, ranging from 
<collectingCountry id="F368DDED772CFF884C2F5FAAFD38AFDE" box="[577,663,403,429]" name="Mexico" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F368DDED772CFF884CD55FAAFCB7AFDE" box="[699,792,403,429]" name="Ecuador" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEEE08C772CFF884D495FAAFB9DAFDE" author="Hiller, A. &amp; Werding, B." box="[807,1074,403,429]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" pagination="181 - 194" refId="ref73657" refString="Hiller, A. &amp; Werding, B. (2007) Redescription of Petrolisthes edwardsii (de Saussure) and description of a new, sibling species from the eastern Pacific based on different colour, morphology and genetic identity (Crustacea: Anomura: Porcellanidae). Organisms Diversity and Evolution, 7 (3), 181 - 194. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ode. 2006.06.002" type="journal article" year="2007">Hiller &amp; Werding 2007</bibRefCitation>
). On the other hand, the identity of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7FE6FE772CFF884EDB5F8EFECEAFA2" baseAuthorityName="de Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[181,353,439,465]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edwardsii">
<emphasis id="B90B416F772CFF884EDB5F8EFF64AFA3" box="[181,203,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">P.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B90B416F772CFF884E9A5F8EFECEAFA2" box="[244,353,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">edwardsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEEE08C772CFF884FE85F8EFCC0AFA2" author="Garcia-Madrigal, M. S. &amp; Andreu-Sanchez, L. I." box="[390,879,439,465]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" pagination="23 - 54" refId="ref71705" refString="Garcia-Madrigal, M. S. &amp; Andreu-Sanchez, L. I. (2009) Los cangrejos porcelanidos (Decapoda: Anomura) del Pacifico sur de Mexico, incluyendo una lista y clave de identificacion para todas las especies del Pacifico oriental tropical. Ciencia y Mar, 13 (39), 23 - 54." type="journal article" year="2009">García-Madrigal &amp; Andréu-Sánchez (2009)</bibRefCitation>
remains uncertain. The same is true for the specimen from 
<collectingRegion id="49BB539F772CFF884F635FE2FE2CAF86" box="[269,387,475,501]" country="Ecuador" name="Galapagos" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Galápagos</collectingRegion>
identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C7FE6FE772CFF884C735FE2FD08AF86" baseAuthorityName="de Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[541,679,475,501]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edwardsii">
<emphasis id="B90B416F772CFF884C735FE2FD08AF86" box="[541,679,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">P. edwardsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEEE08C772CFF884CA25FE2FB98AF86" author="Hickman, C. P. &amp; Zimmerman, T. L." box="[716,1079,475,501]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" refId="ref73387" refString="Hickman, C. P. &amp; Zimmerman, T. L. (2000) A field guide to crustaceans of Galapagos: an illustrated guidebook to the common barnacles, shrimps, lobsters and crabs of the Galapagos Islands. Sugar Spring Press, Lexington, 156 pp." type="book" year="2000">Hickman &amp; Zimmerman (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, with a slightly different colour pattern on the P2–P4 propodi.
</paragraph>
